MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: A single unit of shared resources within a cluster, comprised of one or more containers(Citation: Kube Kubectl)(Citation: Kube Pod)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Pod

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: A standard unit of virtualized software that packages up code and all its dependencies so the application runs quickly and reliably from one computing environment to another(Citation: Docker Docs Container)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Container

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: A profile representing a user, device, service, or application used to authenticate and access resources
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: User Account

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: A Windows OS hierarchical database that stores much of the information and settings for software programs, hardware devices, user preferences, and operating-system configurations(Citation: Microsoft Registry)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Windows Registry

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: A file or stream containing a list of commands, allowing them to be launched in sequence(Citation: Microsoft PowerShell Logging)(Citation: FireEye PowerShell Logging)(Citation: Microsoft AMSI)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Script

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: A single file used to deploy a virtual machine/bootable disk into an on-premise or third-party cloud environment(Citation: Microsoft Image)(Citation: Amazon AMI)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Image

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: Credential material, such as session cookies or tokens, used to authenticate to web applications and services(Citation: Medium Authentication Tokens)(Citation: Auth0 Access Tokens)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Web Credential

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: Mechanisms that allow inter-process communication locally or over the network. A named pipe is usually found as a file and processes attach to it(Citation: Microsoft Named Pipes)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Named Pipe

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: A digital document, which highlights information such as the owner's identity, used to instill trust in public keys used while encrypting network communications
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Certificate

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: The infrastructure for management data and operations that enables local and remote management of Windows personal computers and servers(Citation: Microsoft WMI System Classes)(Citation: Microsoft WMI Architecture)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: WMI

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: Data object storage infrastructure hosted on-premise or by third-party providers, made available to users through network connections and/or APIs(Citation: Amazon S3)(Citation: Azure Blob Storage)(Citation: Google Cloud Storage)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Cloud Storage

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: Information obtained (commonly via active network traffic probes or web crawling) regarding various types of resources and servers connected to the public Internet
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Internet Scan

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: A malicious online profile representing a user commonly used by adversaries to social engineer or otherwise target victims
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Persona

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: A collection of multiple user accounts that share the same access rights to the computer and/or network resources and have common security rights(Citation: Amazon IAM Groups)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Group

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: Events collected by third-party services such as mail servers, web applications, or other appliances (not by the native OS or platform)(Citation: Confluence Logs)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Application Log

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: Logon occurring on a system or resource (local, domain, or cloud) to which a user/device is gaining access after successful authentication and authorization(Citation: Microsoft Audit Logon Events)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Logon Session

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: A virtual server environment which runs workloads, hosted on-premise or by third-party cloud providers(Citation: Amazon VM)(Citation: Google VM)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Instance

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: Information from host telemetry providing insights about system status, errors, or other notable functional activity
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Sensor Health

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: A computer resource object, managed by the I/O system, for storing data (such as images, text, videos, computer programs, or any wide variety of other media).(Citation: Microsoft File Mgmt)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: File

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: A non-volatile data storage device (hard drive, floppy disk, USB flash drive) with at least one formatted partition, typically mounted to the file system and/or assigned a drive letter(Citation: Sysmon EID 9)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Drive

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: A point-in-time copy of cloud volumes (files, settings, etc.) that can be created and/or deployed in cloud environments(Citation: Microsoft Snapshot)(Citation: Amazon Snapshots)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Snapshot

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: A directive given to a computer program, acting as an interpreter of some kind, in order to perform a specific task(Citation: Confluence Linux Command  Line)(Citation: Audit OSX)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Command

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: A computer program, at the core of a computer OS, that resides in memory and facilitates interactions between hardware and software components(Citation: STIG Audit Kernel Modules)(Citation: Init Man Page)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Kernel

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: A computer program that operates or controls a particular type of device that is attached to a computer. Provides a software interface to hardware devices, enabling operating systems and other computer programs to access hardware functions without needing to know precise details about the hardware being used(Citation: IOKit Fundamentals)(Citation: Windows Getting Started Drivers)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Driver

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: Block object storage hosted on-premise or by third-party providers, typically made available to resources as virtualized hard drives(Citation: Amazon S3)(Citation: Azure Blob Storage)(Citation: Google Cloud Storage)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Volume

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: Infrastructure, platforms, or software that are hosted on-premise or by third-party providers, made available to users through network connections and/or APIs(Citation: Amazon AWS)(Citation: Azure Products)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Cloud Service

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: Information obtained (via shared or submitted samples) regarding malicious software (droppers, backdoors, etc.) used by adversaries
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Malware Repository

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: A storage resource (typically a folder or drive) made available from one host to others using network protocols, such as Server Message Block (SMB) or Network File System (NFS)(Citation: Microsoft NFS Overview)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Network Share

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: Data transmitted across a network (ex: Web, DNS, Mail, File, etc.), that is either summarized (ex: Netflow) and/or captured as raw data in an analyzable format (ex: PCAP)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Network Traffic

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: A set of containerized computing resources that are managed together but have separate nodes to execute various tasks and/or applications(Citation: Kube Cluster Admin)(Citation: Kube Cluster Info)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Cluster

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: Automated tasks that can be executed at a specific time or on a recurring schedule running in the background (ex: Cron daemon, task scheduler, BITS)(Citation: Microsoft Tasks)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Scheduled Job

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: Computer software that provides low-level control for the hardware and device(s) of a host, such as BIOS or UEFI/EFI
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Firmware

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: A database and set of services that allows administrators to manage permissions, access to network resources, and stored data objects (user, group, application, or devices)(Citation: Microsoft AD DS Getting Started)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Active Directory

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: A computer process that is configured to execute continuously in the background and perform system tasks, in some cases before any user has logged in(Citation: Microsoft Services)(Citation: Linux Services Run Levels)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Service

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: Information obtained (commonly through registration or activity logs) regarding one or more IP addresses registered with human readable names (ex: mitre.org)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Domain Name

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: Instances of computer programs that are being executed by at least one thread. Processes have memory space for process executables, loaded modules (DLLs or shared libraries), and allocated memory regions containing everything from user input to application-specific data structures(Citation: Microsoft Processes and Threads)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Process

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: A network security system, running locally on an endpoint or remotely as a service (ex: cloud environment), that monitors and controls incoming/outgoing network traffic based on predefined rules(Citation: AWS Sec Groups VPC)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Firewall

MITRE_Data_Sources.Description: Executable files consisting of one or more shared classes and interfaces, such as portable executable (PE) format binaries/dynamic link libraries (DLL), executable and linkable format (ELF) binaries/shared libraries, and Mach-O format binaries/shared libraries(Citation: Microsoft LoadLibrary)(Citation: Microsoft Module Class)
MITRE_Data_Sources.Name: Module

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: A user requested active directory credentials, such as a ticket or token (ex: Windows EID 4769)
MITRE_Data_Component.Name: Active Directory Credential Request

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Initial construction of a WMI object, such as a filter, consumer, subscription, binding, or provider (ex: Sysmon EIDs 19-21)
MITRE_Data_Component.Name: WMI Creation

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Changes made to a group, such as membership, name, or permissions (ex: Windows EID 4728 or 4732, AWS IAM UpdateGroup)
MITRE_Data_Component.Name: Group Modification

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Changes made to a virtual machine image, including setting and/or control data (ex: Azure Compute Service Images PATCH)
MITRE_Data_Component.Name: Image Modification

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: An extracted list of pods within a cluster (ex: kubectl get pods)
MITRE_Data_Component.Name: Pod Enumeration

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Logged network traffic in response to a scan showing both protocol header and body values
MITRE_Data_Component.Name: Response Content

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Contextual data about a cloud volume and activity around it, such as id, type, state, and size
MITRE_Data_Component.Name: Volume Metadata

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Contextual data about an Internet-facing resource gathered from a scan, such as running services or ports
MITRE_Data_Component.Name: Response Metadata

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Removal of a Registry Key (ex: Windows EID 4658 or Sysmon EID 12)

MITRE_Data_Component.Name: Snapshot Deletion

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Opening of a process by another process, typically to read memory of the target process (ex: Sysmon EID 10)

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Initial construction of a new active directory object (ex: Windows EID 5137)

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Queried or logged information highlighting current and expired digital certificates (ex: Certificate transparency)

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Opening a file, which makes the file contents available to the requestor (ex: Windows EID 4663)

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: An object file that contains code to extend the running kernel of an OS, typically used to add support for new hardware (as device drivers) and/or filesystems, or for adding system calls

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: An extracted list of instances within a cloud environment (ex: instance.list within GCP Audit Logs)

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Initial construction of a new file (ex: Sysmon EID 11)

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Queried domain name system (DNS) registry data highlighting current domain to IP address resolutions (ex: dig/nslookup queries)

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Attaching a driver to either user or kernel-mode of a system (ex: Sysmon EID 6)

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Logged network traffic data showing both protocol header and body values (ex: PCAP)
MITRE_Data_Component.Name: Network Traffic Content

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Removal of a a cloud volume (ex: AWS delete-volume)

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Initial construction of a drive letter or mount point to a data storage device

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Changes made to an active directory object (ex: Windows EID 5163 or 5136)

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Initial construction of a new Registry Key (ex: Windows EID 4656 or Sysmon EID 12)

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Changes made to a cloud service, including its settings and/or data (ex: AWS CloudTrail DeleteTrail or DeleteConfigRule)
MITRE_Data_Component.Name: Cloud Service Modification

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Removal of a file (ex: Sysmon EID 23, macOS ESF EID ES_EVENT_TYPE_AUTH_UNLINK, or Linux commands auditd unlink, rename, rmdir, unlinked, or renameat rules)
MITRE_Data_Component.Name: File Deletion

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Deactivation or stoppage of a cloud service (ex: AWS Cloudtrail StopLogging)
MITRE_Data_Component.Name: Cloud Service Disable

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: An extracted list of available volumes within a cloud environment (ex: AWS describe-volumes)
MITRE_Data_Component.Name: Volume Enumeration

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Opening a Registry Key, typically to read the associated value (ex: Windows EID 4656)
MITRE_Data_Component.Name: Windows Registry Key Access

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Contextual data about a running process, which may include information such as environment variables, image name, user/owner, etc.
MITRE_Data_Component.Name: Process Metadata

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Changes made to a snapshop, such as metadata and control data (ex: AWS modify-snapshot-attribute)
MITRE_Data_Component.Name: Snapshot Modification

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Initial construction of a new scheduled job (ex: Windows EID 4698 or /var/log cron logs)
MITRE_Data_Component.Name: Scheduled Job Creation

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Opening a network share, which makes the contents available to the requestor (ex: Windows EID 5140 or 5145)
MITRE_Data_Component.Name: Network Share Access

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Contextual data about a driver and activity around it such as driver issues reporting or integrity (page hash, code) checking
MITRE_Data_Component.Name: Driver Metadata

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Activation or invocation of an instance (ex: instance.start within GCP Audit Logs)
MITRE_Data_Component.Name: Instance Start

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Changes made to a scheduled job, such as modifications to the execution launch (ex: Windows EID 4702 or /var/log cron logs)
MITRE_Data_Component.Name: Scheduled Job Modification

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Contextual data about a cluster and activity around it such as name, namespace, age, or status
MITRE_Data_Component.Name: Cluster Metadata

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: An extracted list of cloud storage infrastructure (ex: AWS S3 ListBuckets or ListObjects)
MITRE_Data_Component.Name: Cloud Storage Enumeration

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: An attempt by a user to gain access to a network or computing resource by providing web credentials (ex: Windows EID 1202)
MITRE_Data_Component.Name: Web Credential Usage

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: Information about domain name assignments and other domain metadata (ex: WHOIS)
MITRE_Data_Component.Name: Domain Registration

MITRE_Data_Component.Description: An extracted list of snapshops within a cloud environment (ex: AWS describe-snapshots)
MITRE_Data_Component.Name: Snapshot Enumeration
